msgid ""
"Profiles are used to specify the appearance of a specific widget, "
"including its shape,  color, text(s) or element(s) inside… Each widget's "
"profiles are stored in attribute  `profiles`, in form of `{\"state "
"name\": WidgetProfile()}`."
msgstr ""

#: charmy.widgets.widget.Widget.__init__:9 of
msgid ""
"Each widget comes with default profiles config, which can be changed by "
"specifying  `profiles` when initializing them. Contents specified in "
"`profiles` arg will override  defaults (Note: minimum overriding unit is "
"a `WidgetProfile` instance specified for a  specific state)."
msgstr ""

